Barack Obama is the fourth U.S. president to win the Nobel Peace Prize
US President Barack Obama comes to Oslo, Norway, for 26 hours, to receive the Nobel Peace Prize as the fourth US president in history.
In addition, he receives the diploma as well as the medal and a cheque of $1.4 million for his extraordinary efforts to intensify world diplomacy and cooperation among peoples.
The head of the White House arrives tomorrow with his wife Michelle in the north-west of the city and will be busy all the time.
First, he visits the Nobel Institute, where he meets for the first time with the five committee members who elected him in October from 172 people and 33 organizations.
The Presidential couple then planned a meeting with Norwegian King Harald V and Queen Sonja.
In the afternoon, the visit reaches its peak with the ceremony in which Obama takes over the prestige prize.
He is the fourth President of the United States, but only the third to receive the prize directly in office.
The White House has already announced that Obama will talk about the Afghanistan war when he takes over the prize.
The president does not want to avoid this issue because he knows that he is taking the prize as a president who is currently waging war in two countries.
A few days ago, he reinforced the war effort by sending more troops to Afghanistan, which none of his critics forget to highlight.
At the ceremony, Obama also received the gold medal, diploma and cheque for ten million Swedish crowns (about 24 million Czech crowns).
He intends to donate the money for charitable purposes, but he has not yet decided on a concrete charitable work.
The event programme then provides for a banquet with the President and his wife, in which, apart from Norway’s King and Queen, the Prime Minister and a further 250 invited guests will be present.
Obama was very cautious from the start.
For example, he stated that he felt that he did not fully deserve the prize.
He also repeated several times that it is not only for him, but for all those who aspire to the same values as him.
Immediately after the announcement, he stated that this is for him "invitation of action".
