The political institutions, even if formally founded correctly, remain only sham buildings, behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the various ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the intransigence of the conditions that further complicate the influences of Pakistan and Iran.
The creation of a “capable state”, which is the minimalist goal of the entire operation, is also very unrealistic.
