Vaccination against pneumococcal free and voluntary
Vaccination against pneumococcal disease will change the usual from January.
It is the first to be free and voluntary for families.
But already, voices are reporting that the mandatory vaccination would be more effective.
The preparations for the introduction of the free vaccination against pneumococcal disease culminate.
The Institute of Medicine has already set the maximum prices of the vaccines that health insurance must pay.
