Although officials from a rural small town in the outskirts of Shanghai said that an upswing in the applications of couples who want a second child after the start of the campaign can be seen, the urban districts do not report any change.
In the municipality of Huinan with a population of 115,000, as an example, only four to five applications are received per month.
Disappointed Shanghai officials say the expected number of births in the city in 2010 despite the campaign will still be about 165,000 -- slightly higher than in 2009, but lower than in 2008.
